thread.title_full: Are these the funniest school yearbook entries yet?

title: Are these the funniest school yearbook entries yet?
text: Share this article Share Relative values! Four girls with the same surname made sure that nobody could mistake them for sisters Jaime Mendoza wasn't afraid to make reference to his rather prominent ears Allison's identical twin Lauren longs for the very brief period of time before her sister was born Randey Chung does not look back on his experience of high school with extreme fondness Hair raising! Julianna Massa wasn't afraid to joke about her lack of locks Segun jokingly likened himself to a Nigerian 419 scam Steven and his friend Kristian went out of the way to make things confusing Christopher is now out and proud - especially of his fashion sense He's no Zac Efron: High school was far from a Disney-style musical for Seth Confession time! This student decided to take the opportunity to reveal his most unusual hobby He may be vegetarian, but that doesn't make Ankit cute and cuddlty Nicole's motivational quote feel somewhat flat after she revealed it came from a video game character In an ideal world Aditya would have liked to be a lot more verbose with his parting statement Heart of stone: Jessica proved that she's not one for romance with her high school yearbook parting thoughts He's heard that one before! Joe McDonald was clearly fed up with nursery rhyme-based jokes Nick put an unexpected twist on the classic rhyme to go with his photo Max used his yearbook message to make a quirky statement about his taste in partners Is that you mom? Zachary couldn't help pointing out his strange resemblance to a single mother My precious! Lord of the Rings fan Megan referenced her favourite novel and film in her parting shot Daniel's father has high hopes for his son, despite the fact he's only just graduated from high school Antony has the dubious pleasure of always being under some kind of suspicion Time for a deed poll change? Christopher made reference to his somewhat unusual surname Brooke's profile (left) ended up above Blake's prompting him to resort to sexual innuendo Conner Hart made a very cheeky reference to his daily routine Against his mother's advice, Griffin went for a photo that showed off his outdoorsy side The end of high school felt like getting out of jail for a relieved Faizon Only one of these twins was expected, but Rebecca seems to take it in good spirits This boy had a message for female admirers who might not be instantly bowled over by his curly locks The title of wrestler John Cena's debut album came in handy for Maliha Lord Of The Rings fan Jucinda was utterly thrilled not to flunk Irfan had a unique explanation for not achieving the results he'd hoped for Sorry dad! Xenia refused to listen to advice from her father on what to write Michelle decided to poke fun at her surname before anyone else could Motivational! Mitchell had some wise words for his fellow high school alumni As long as you can say her name right, Agboke will be happy Triplets turned their graduation triptych into a knock knock joke Referencing her cup size, this student explained why she hadn't achieved the results she'd hoped Paige outdid everyone by managing to get smileys and animal emojis into her yearbook Too much time in the gym? It seems that Eric might have missed out on some crucial grammar lessons Yunosuke turned the motivational slogan on his head with his musings about rubbish After years of enduring the same name and surname, Carlos finally snapped Barry took the opportunity to send a message to his future children This teen did not mince her words when it came to summing up her years of education Even if you're not very good at maths, you can always rely on counting on your fingers according to Bumb Just add shades! Daniel decided to pose as his less cool alter ego
